o new trades from August 2010 namely certificate in software programming,Multimedia and Desktop Publishing. By August 2013,The institute is introducing 2 new trades for women,namely hair and skin care and fashion technology with ace or art technology imported machinary.',_binary '...','Government',NULL,2001,NULL,NULL,'https://mahilaitirajkotcity.gujarat.gov.in/',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N',NULL),('ORG00003','enuk','Life Women Empowerment Center','Life Women Empowerment Centre (LWEC) is a unique intervention imparting free vocational training to less privileged women & widows in skills leading to self-reliance, social respect and support to their families, generating self-confidence, improved medical care and better education for children. Free trade kits, equipment and market linkage are provided to pave the way to productive employment. The programme also covers supplementary training in self-defense, gender equality, budgeting, banking and finance for self-sufficiency and personality development, leading to holistic empowerment. ',_binary '...','NGO',NULL,1978,NULL,NULL,'https://life4life.org.in/home',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N',NULL),('ORG00004','enuk','Chetna','CHETNA is managed by a women-led core management team, governed by a governing council and comprises a team that has academic and research experts in the field of health, nutrition of women, children and young people, education, communication, and gender. CHETNA reaches out to more than 36 Districts, 1930 villages in three States pan India through its programmes and publications.',_binary '...','NGO',NULL,1980,NULL,NULL,'https://www.chetnaindia.org/what-we-do/',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N',NULL),('ORG00005','enuk','WOMEN & CHILD DEVELOPMENT DEPARTMENT (WCD)  GOVERNMENT OF GUJARAT','This organization intends to ensure childrenâ€™s nutrition and empower woman living with dignity and ensure nutrition and development of woman in an environment free from violence and discrimination.Goals: To improve the nutritional and health status of children in the age group of 0-6 years.To lay the foundation for the proper psychological, physical and social development of the child.To reduce the incidence of mortality, morbidity, and malnutrition.To enhance the capability of the mother to look after the normal health and nutrition health of the child through proper nutrition and health education.Provide essential health services to young children, pregnant and pregnant mothers and adolescent girls lactating mothers and adolescent girls through Anganwadi.Providing preprimary education for children aged 3-6 years in Anganwadi.To prevent female feticide and to ensure the survival, education and protection of the girl child.To economically empower destitute widows by providing them with financial assistance and vocational training.To provide shelter, police desk, legal, medical and counselling services to woman or child victims of violence under one roof integrated with a 24*7 Helpline.To prevent the trafficking of women for commercial sexual exploitation and to facilitate the reintegration of the victims into the family and society.To promote the availability of safe and conveniently located accommodation for working women with daycare facilities for their children.To cater to the primary need of shelter, food, clothing, medical treatment and care of women in distress and those who are without any social and economic support.To create an alternative system of justice for the woman that gives quick justice to the woman in a minimum cost with understanding their feelings.To promote birth rate of girl child with schemes like VahaliDikari Scheme.',_binary '...','Government',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'https://wcd.gujarat.gov.in/posts?id=483',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N',NULL),('ORG00006','enuk','Manav Kartavya NGO','Founded in 2015, Manav Kartavya is an Ahmedabad, Gujarat, India, based Non-Governmental Organization (NGO) committed to helping disadvantaged beings. Each day represents a fresh opportunity to share our Vision of creating, â€˜The Advantaged Societyâ€™; and to live our purpose of empowering the possibilities for economically weaker communities by supporting them with basic necessities such as education, food, health, shelter, etc. to empower them to take charge of their own future as our Mission.',_binary '...','NGO',NULL,2015,NULL,NULL,'http://manavkartavya.org/about-us/',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N',NULL),('ORG00007','enuk','Gujarat Rajya Gram Vikas Samiti','\nGujarat Rajya Gram Vikas Samiti is a Public Trust (NGO) serving since 1988. GRGVS has FCRA, CSR 1, 12AA, 80G certifications. It is registered under Bombay Public Trust Act, 1950 and Societies Registration Act, 1860. GRGVS has registrations with Niti Aaayog and has partnered with various Government Organizations and companies.',_binary '...','NGO',NULL,1988,NULL,NULL,'https://gujaratgramvikas.org/about/','@Gujaratgramvikas ',NULL,NULL,'N',NULL),('ORG00008','enuk','Friends Care Foundation ','Friends Care Foundation is a Non-Governmental Organization established under Society Registration Act, 1860 and The Bombay Public Trust Act, 1950 based in Ahmedabad, Gujarat, India. Fostering a society wherein women are empowered enough to add value to their family and society; all children are empowered with education and enjoy their childhood rights, and creating a sustainable and humane society wherein all living being have access to manage their livelihood. Plan and implement or join hands with government, donors, non-government and other Volunteer bodies for implementing, a development that fulfils our vision to educate, organize, and strengthen the downtrodden communities with total capacities to manage their own development. Friends Care Foundation is focused on Orphanage Support, Child Rights, Education Support, Old Age Support, Women Empowerment, Calamity Relief, Medical Support and Care of Birds & Animals.',_binary '...','NGO',NULL,1950,NULL,NULL,'https://www.friendscarefoundation.org/about-us/',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N',NULL),('ORG00009','enuk','A